<recipe>
<title>
Dr Pepper Barbecue Sauce
</title>
<details>
AUTHOR: i heart eating
PREP TIME: 10 minutes
COOK TIME: 20 minutes
TOTAL TIME: 30 minutes
COURSE: Sauce
CUISINE: American
KEYWORD: barbecue
SERVINGS: 8
</details>
<ingredients><ingredient amount="0.5 C ">Sugar</ingredient><ingredient amount="6.0 oz ">Tomato Paste</ingredient><ingredient amount="1.0 tsp ">Chili Powder</ingredient><ingredient amount="1.0 tsp ">Garlic</ingredient><ingredient amount="0.5 tsp ">Pepper</ingredient></ingredients>
<instructions>
Add all the ingredients to a saucepan, and stir until combined.
Let the sauce simmer for 20-30 minutes, or until it begins to thicken, stirring occasionally.
Taste and adjust the seasonings with additional salt and pepper, if desired.
Let sauce cool until room temperature.
Cover, and store, refrigerated, for up to 2 weeks.
</instructions>
<cuisine>American</cuisine></recipe>